reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars No Frills, Solid Performance, Whisper Quiet
reviews.reviewText: Must say I wasn't expecting much.The price kind of made me think "Brace yourself, it's gonna be loud".Boy I was wrong....These fans are superb. They are so quiet that at first I thought I missed the motherboard connectors. I love they have rubber paddings to prevent vibration and they have significantly improved the airflow in my mATX case.I absolutely HATE these fans that are filled with LEDs, but if that is your thing, keep in mind these are BLACK, NO LED, type of deal. To me, that's a winning solution.I highly recommend. This s the best bang for your buck you will get on amazon!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Not the best but best for the price --- QUIET
reviews.reviewText: Like i said, if you buy these expecting them to be like noctua then you will be disappointed. At the price of 13 dollars 3 120mm fans that at max speed are honestly not loud at all. they do however move a fair amount of air. I have all 4 fan mounts filled with these fans and i have no complaints. few months gone by and still quiet and effective. i will definitely recommend these and ill buy them again eventually. literally my one and only CON is build quality. the fans fell like they could snap quite easily if you bend them. again however i cant fault the product for that because no pc fan is ment to bend so all in all ill have to give it 5/5 even if they die in 1 year itll be a 5/5 because that price is unbeatable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Don't know about for building a new pc, or how these compare to other fans, but they move air and haven't broken down since months of use yet.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great fans at an excellent price
reviews.reviewText: I originally purchased a set of these for my son's new (at the time) build because I needed something fast and inexpensive that would work "for now". I was surprised to see how effective the rubber damping pads were, and the wiring was nice and long. The fans also exceeded my expectations with how quiet they were, while remaining effective.I purchased another set for my TrueNAS build and they worked out so well that I recently grabbed another set and, you guessed it, they work great too!Pros: Very effective; Quiet; Rubber Damping Pads; Long Wires; InexpensiveCons: None.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works as advertised
reviews.reviewText: All 3 are still working about a year in. The rubber pads on each screw location are an appreciated feature that reduces noise/vibration. Easy to install but nothing particularly notable about them.

Llegaron antes de tiempo. Se ven bien construidos por el precio. Son para un update de una pc de hace 10 año.

Overall very easy to install. I daisy-chained them directly to the power supply. I added those 3 fans on top of the 4 already in my pc (3 intake, 1 exhaust) so it’s now 4 intake (1 fan is stacked on top of another) and 3 exhaust fans.Now, the back of the computer is not as hot as before and more hot air can be pushed from the top. All my fans spin slower which reduces the noise level. Also, there is noticeably less dust inside due to the difference of pressure!I’m very happy about this purchase. The fans are quiet and very easy to install.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on December 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: Decent extra case fans, easy to use
reviews.reviewText: These are reasonably good extra 120mm case fans for a pc tower build. The airflow is increased, they improve cooling and they are not loud at all. I found the fans easy to fit, decent quality and had no problems at all installing and using them very quickly.I would recommend them if you are after some good value fans to improve airflow in your pc build. There are better fans out there but you will pay more for them and if you are on a budget these are definitely better than not having extra fans in your machine.
